<subSubSection id="0FD0E0E14531E94437FD9760F4E00EB4" pageId="34" pageNumber="85" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="41C9F65D09400193436EF6B7356FCFCA" pageId="34" pageNumber="85">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E618915573B8CA77387CBAFAC5BD1057" pageId="34" pageNumber="85">The name is derived from the Malay word merah (red), and refers to the red or orange colour of the male pedipalps. Gender feminine.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="093551A5F4D809E9C28DB9281ACF948F" pageId="34" pageNumber="85" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A8603DCCD64F4717E835951451DA4F77" pageId="34" pageNumber="85">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="22D3FE08AEFFE6A4F5D99390FB253CCE" pageId="34" pageNumber="85">
Medium size, light coloured pholcids with long legs and cylindrical abdomen (
<bibRefCitation id="93245CCA8E330D73A310886996D8C003" author="Huber, BA" journalOrPublisher="European Journal of Taxonomy" pageId="42" pageNumber="93" pagination="1 - 55" title="The Southeast Asian Pholcushalabala species group (Araneae, Pholcidae), new data from field observations and ultrastructure." url="https://doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2016.190" volume="190" year="2016 a">Huber et al. 2016a</bibRefCitation>
: figs 102-109); distinguished from similar species in other genera (
<taxonomicName id="85DA097CA34D171087B17D3928C2F545" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Kelabita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Kelabita" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Kelabita</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1A3D0C2E8A50C97A8C19B8D34FFEAF49" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Apokayana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Apokayana" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Apokayana</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9533011944B6636FA485664BCDA3B645" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Teranga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teranga" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Teranga</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="62C173A49378AEF1D0A409A9825A8A30" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Muruta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Muruta" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Muruta</taxonomicName>
) by combination of: six eyes; absence of modified hairs on distal male cheliceral apophyses (
<bibRefCitation id="1C4882392D032CB46C2586E6A3117F0B" author="Huber, BA" journalOrPublisher="European Journal of Taxonomy" pageId="42" pageNumber="93" pagination="1 - 55" title="The Southeast Asian Pholcushalabala species group (Araneae, Pholcidae), new data from field observations and ultrastructure." url="https://doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2016.190" volume="190" year="2016 a">Huber et al. 2016a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 118); reduction of ALS spigots to two (
<bibRefCitation id="9D27F87BAF73D700A12706A208AE19CB" author="Huber, BA" journalOrPublisher="Bonner zoologische Monographien" pageId="40" pageNumber="91" pagination="1 - 509" title="Revision and cladistic analysis of Pholcus and closely related taxa (Araneae, Pholcidae)." volume="58" year="2011 a">Huber 2011a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 566, 
<bibRefCitation id="0C0935DFAF610B58D98812C80666A155" author="Huber, BA" journalOrPublisher="European Journal of Taxonomy" pageId="42" pageNumber="93" pagination="1 - 55" title="The Southeast Asian Pholcushalabala species group (Araneae, Pholcidae), new data from field observations and ultrastructure." url="https://doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2016.190" volume="190" year="2016 a">Huber et al. 2016a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 122); reddish to orange male palps (
<bibRefCitation id="4AB0169E0DDB387F66302867B2A46EFB" author="Huber, BA" journalOrPublisher="European Journal of Taxonomy" pageId="42" pageNumber="93" pagination="1 - 55" title="The Southeast Asian Pholcushalabala species group (Araneae, Pholcidae), new data from field observations and ultrastructure." url="https://doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2016.190" volume="190" year="2016 a">Huber et al. 2016a</bibRefCitation>
: figs 102, 106, 108). In the field they can be distinguished from most other genera (except 
<taxonomicName id="3DB3AED8EF6543A359E298BB6F135F8D" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Kelabita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Kelabita" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Kelabita</taxonomicName>
) by their domed webs relatively high among the vegetation (0.5-2 m above the ground), usually with the apex of the dome attached to the underside of a leaf.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9BEDA63524D659B891AA15AC535878A7" pageId="34" pageNumber="85" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="368F0C0BE95B6F2C9FEE6E07BAF2D545" pageId="34" pageNumber="85">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9ADDC476739443553A8367E2A160AF84" pageId="34" pageNumber="85">
Mainland Southeast Asia and Borneo (
<bibRefCitation id="6115A538FDC238A2359A85A8BC005042" author="Huber, BA" journalOrPublisher="European Journal of Taxonomy" pageId="42" pageNumber="93" pagination="1 - 55" title="The Southeast Asian Pholcushalabala species group (Araneae, Pholcidae), new data from field observations and ultrastructure." url="https://doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2016.190" volume="190" year="2016 a">Huber et al. 2016a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 110).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EFB54D1F51C7F30A820613DB00B3C372" pageId="34" pageNumber="85" type="composition">
<paragraph id="72EA190F63676869A2A68D9F63BB86A3" pageId="34" pageNumber="85">Composition.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D53C9F544B07087795897E2010972DA1" pageId="34" pageNumber="85">
